    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL 4X2 AND 6X4 SPRING SUSPENSION WITH TORQUE RODS - SERVICE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>SERVICE</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s03008_8.xml" xrefid="f0300807">Figure 7</hotlnk>and
                <hotlnk document="s03008_8.xml" xrefid="f0300808">Figure 8</hotlnk>to aid in service procedures.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0300804" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg03/G0300804.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Equalizer Components</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SPRING RETAINER PINS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. EQUALIZER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. EQUALIZER BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. ADAPTER</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. PIVOT BOLT/NUT AND LOCKWASHER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0300805" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg03/G0300805.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. Equalizer Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. EQUALIZER BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. EQUALIZER ADAPTER BUSHING</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. EQUALIZER</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. EQUALIZER BEARING (BUSHING)</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. SPRING RETAINER PIN</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. BOLT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>When assembling spring leaves, be careful to prevent physical injury to personnel. The use of
                        special holding fixtures or "C" clamps for holding spring leaves in place during assembly is
                        strongly recommended.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
